'''Callington Town Football Club''' is a [[Association Football|football]] club based in [[Callington, Cornwall|Callington]], [[Cornwall]], England. They are currently members of {{English football updater|CallingT}} and play at Marshfield Parc.

==History==
The club was established in 1989 and joined the [[East Cornwall League|East Cornwall Combination]] the following year.<ref>[http://www.cornishguardian.co.uk/football-callington-confirm-metters-appointment/story-29372219-detail/story.html Football: Callington confirm Metters appointment - June 8] Cornwall Guardian, 8 June 2016</ref><ref name=NLM>[http://www.nonleaguematters.co.uk/nlmnet/Aarg3EC/ECC86.html East Cornwall Combination 1986-2007] Non-League Matters</ref> They were runners-up in 1994–95 and went on to win back-to-back league titles in 1997–98 and 1998–99.<ref name=NLM/> After their second East Cornwall Combination title they moved up to the [[South Western Football League|South Western League]], where they spent several seasons in lower-mid table, finishing bottom of the league in 2003–04.<ref name=FCHD>{{fchd|id=CALLINTT|name=Callington Town}}</ref>

In 2007 Callington became founder members of the [[South West Peninsula League]], and were placed in Division One West. In [[2013–14 South West Peninsula League|2013–14]] the club won the division, earning promotion to the Premier Division;<ref name=FCHD/> they also won the Cornwall Charity Cup, beating [[Dobwalls F.C.|Dobwalls]] 1–0 in the final after extra time.<ref>[http://www.cornwalllive.com/farnham-s-late-late-goal-seals-charity-cup/story-21068664-detail/story.html Farnham's late late goal seals Charity Cup success for Callington] Cornwall Live, 7 May 2014</ref> The [[2014–15 South West Peninsula League|following season]] saw them win the league's Charity Vase with a win over [[Stoke Gabriel A.F.C.|Stoke Gabriel]].<ref>[http://www.swpleague.co.uk/league/previous-league-cup-winners/ League Honours] South West Peninsula League</ref>

==Honours==
*'''South West Peninsula League'''
**Division One West Champions 2013–14
**Charity Vase winners 2014–15
*'''East Cornwall Combination'''
**Champions 1997–98, 1998–99
*'''Cornwall Charity Cup'''
**Winners 2013–14

